\fB\-itmx GiB\fR, \fB\-\-ec2-instance-type-memory-max-gigabytes-per-core GiB\fR
This option is used to specify the maximum size memory and is used in conjunction with the  \fB\-\-ec2-instance-type-memory-min-gigabytes-per-core \fR to define a memory size range that is to be selected.
The \fBec2\fR object is to filter out instance-types with a memory size that is not within the specified range.

Default: (defined in the system configuration)
